Does anybody know a reference for the following (very easy) result?

Let C and D be categories, and let F:C-->D and G:D-->C be functors.

If (c,theta) is an initial algebra for GF, then (Fc, F theta) is an initi=
al algebra for FG.

thanks,
Paul




